Package com.taco.suit_lady.view.ui.jfx.button

Class ImageButton

java.lang.Object
com.taco.suit_lady.view.ui.jfx.button.ImageButton
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.taco.util.obj_traits.common.Nameable
public class ImageButton extends Object implements com.taco.util.obj_traits.common.Nameable
Class that wraps an ImageView and Button into a single class. Note that ImageButton does not implement or extend any UI framework classes, but rather has methods that allow it to be used in JFX UI environments. At some point, it might be a good idea to change that, allowing ImageButtons to be added directly to the JFX UI and have their functionality handled internally. Currently, the ImageButton is handled by passing a ImagePane object as a parameter that will be responsible for containing the ImageButton. In the future, combining those two classes would likely be preferred, with the image itself being controlled/switched via cache references.
